The paper deals with image super resolution, which is a classic problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The Fields of Experts (FoE) model is a trainable filter-based higher-order Markov Random Fields (MRFs) model, which is a popular model in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of MAP inference, which is a common technique in information theory (cs.IT) and optimization (cs.MM).
